Prof. Emeka Oguzie has been appointed as the Deputy Vice-Chancellor, Research, Development and Innovation by the Federal University of Technology, Owerri. His appointment was announced on Monday, by the Vice-Chancellor of the university, Prof. Nnenna Otti, after a crucial meeting of the university’s senate. His appointment had taken immediate effect with the two other appointed DVC (Academic) and DVC (Administration). Oguzie who is the President of the International Family Foundation featured on the list drawn from the various scientific field including the Department of Civil Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Physics and Chemistry Engineering, Biosciences and Bioengineering, Chemistry Electrical and Electronics. In his congratulatory message, the Secretary of the International Family Foundation, Sir Oviel Omeleh, felicitated with the Board of Trustees and member of the Foundation for such a rare honour done on the Foundation. The message reads, “I congratulate our President for a well-deserved appointment and wish him success in his new arrangement.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com